Oct 14 2009 	Strange Room But Otherwise Nice--And Good Location	We stayed here for one night en route to another destination. Its primary advantage is that it is close to the airport. The airport shuttle worked well for us. The hotel staff were friendly, and the overall quality of the hotel is good. If you are looking for a place to stay that will give you easy access to the major sites of Beijing, this is not the right place, but for access to the airport it is great. The only thing that really put us off (but it put us off quite a lot) was the strange bathroom. I don't know if all rooms are this way, but ours had a large window from the bathroom into the bedroom--basically, the whole wall was a window. This is not a plus in my book, though somebody obviously thought it was. There were blinds that you could close over the window, which was fine unless either the blinds did not close tightly, or a piece of one of the slats was missing. In our case, the blinds had both features, which meant that there was not very good privacy in the bathroom. Maybe I'm a privacy freak, but come on. Other than that, the room was fine, and the hotel served its purpose. I'd still probably recommend it--but hey, fix those blinds!	
