Sep 18 2009 	Great location for an exhibition hotel; terrible location for sightseeing	Stayed here for 6 nights in September for an exhibition at the NCIEC. Location is close to the exhibition centre, but still not really walking distance, especially since our event used the north entrance. There are also not a great deal of amenities in the area, plus walking anywhere aroud there is risky (from a traffic perspective). It is clear that the area is still being developed, so maybe local amenities and pedestrian friendly access will improve over time. Many attendees did some sightseeing before, after, or during the exhibition. It's a long cab ride to central Beijing: anywhere from 40 minutes to well over an hour, depending on traffic. If being a tourist is your main reason for being in Beijing, stay elsewhere. If you're coming for the Exhibition Centre, or need a hotel relatively close to the airport, then this is a good one. (Attendees staying at other, more central hotels had to leave an hour earlier than we did in the morning just to get to the Exhibition Centre in time.)The staff were all extremely polite and usually quite effective. However, they were also fairly slow, at least by North American standards. Drinks in the lounge or restaurant definitely took their time in coming. English proficiency was a problem for some, but many others seemed to have a good grasp of the language. Food in the Crowne Cafe was pretty good, with quite a large variety of Asian and western foods, especially for the buffet breakfast. Had a standard room which met all my requirements, but wasn't anything over and above what I'd expect from a hotel like this (in room safe, nice bathroom, internet...) although it did still smell fairly new. My only real complaint about the room itself was the shower... Water leaked through the shower door and onto the floor. Others indicated the same thing occurred in their rooms as well. I thought the fitness centre was rather small, but in retrospect, in the times that I used it, I never did see people having to wait to use equipment. There is a sauna and steam room as well, but both were cold when I was there, and I didn't feel like waiting for them to warm up. The equipment is very good quality and appears well maintained. Bring your headphones and you can watch an individual TV on the cardio equipment. On the way back home, a colleague and I used the hotel's shuttle to the airport. No problems at all. It left when they said it would and took us right to Terminal 3 (after fighting some traffic).	
